from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import math
import pandas as pd
from scipy.optimize import curve_fit
from mpmath import *
import cmath
i=complex(0,1)

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

ax.plot(f,Rs, color='b', label='Real Part,Resistance')
ax2=ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(f,Zs,color='r',label='Imaginary Part,Reactance')

plt.title('Impedance vs. Frequency for Short Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Re(Impedance) (ohms)')
ax2.set_ylabel('Im(Impedance) (ohms)')

ax2.legend(loc='upper left')
ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.4, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)
ax2.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.4, .7), shadow=True, ncol=1)

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

a=5.528*10**(-10)
b=5.507*10**(-8)
y=76*np.tanh((a+b*i)*f)
plt.plot(f,y.real,label='Resistance')
plt.plot(f,y.imag,label='Reactance')
plt.title('Model for short Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Resistance (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper right')

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

a=5.528*10**(-10)
b=5.507*10**(-8)
y=76*np.tanh((a+b*i)*f)
plt.plot(f,y.real,label='Resistance')
plt.plot(f,y.imag,label='Reactance')
plt.scatter(f,Rs,s=1,label='Measured Resistance')
plt.scatter(f,Zs,s=1,label='Measured Reactance')
plt.title('Model vs Measurement for short Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Resistance (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper right')

plt.title('Low-Loss Best Fit for Reactance of Short Cable')

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

y=Retanh(f,8.75e-10,5.792e-08)
plt.plot(f,y,color='orange',label='Best Fit')
plt.scatter(f,Rs,label='Measurements')

plt.title('Low-Loss Best Fit for Resistance of Short Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Resistance (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper right')
